    "outlook": "Indian equities closed lower, with Nifty 50 and Sensex both in the red, largely driven by significant declines in banking, financial services, auto, and realty sectors. Despite this broad weakness, Metal and Pharma sectors demonstrated resilience, ending the day with notable gains. Continued FII selling, partially cushioned by DII buying, contributed to the subdued market sentiment.",
    "keyTakeaways": [
      "Nifty 50 and Sensex registered declines of 0.53% and 0.67% respectively.",
      "Banking, Financial Services, Auto, and Realty sectors were major laggards.",
      "Metal (+1.04%) and Pharma (+0.77%) sectors outperformed the broader market.",
      "FIIs remained net sellers with an outflow of over 3000 crore.",
      "Market breadth was negative, with 37 declining stocks against 21 advancing.",
      "HCLTech, Bajaj Finance, and DLF were among top losers, while Hindalco and Divi's Lab led gainers."
